6:
It seems I need to reevaluate your
offensive capabilities.
9:
You sure that's the only thing you
need to worry about?
11:
If you're referring to my job security, I
assure you it is more than safe.
19: You won't fight until the end?
21:
I have orders to let you through if I
am rendered incapable of combat.
25:
Orders from above, huh? Sounds like
someone needs a healthy dose of
freedom.
29: I have no need for such freedom.
34:
You will soon see for yourself what
your so-called freedom gives you.
41:
Is it just me, or has the vibe of this
place totally changed?
44:
It seems there is a large wall
obstructing our path ahead.
48:
ANOTHER wall? Man, someone really
doesn't want us here, do they?
53:
Looks like we've got no choice but to
blast it to kingdom—
55: Still trigger-happy as usual, I see.
63:
Were you not curious, Bulleta? Why
you were able to make it this far and
face such little resistance?
66:
I am Mother Love, the president of
DayAndNight. The matriarch of the
undying night.
74:
Poor, poor, Bulleta. How does it feel
to realize how small you are?
79:
This is our first IRL meetup... so take it
easy, won'tcha?
82:
This IS me taking it easy. Especially
to someone attempting to infiltrate
my business.
86: Why... Why are you doing this?
90:
I'm merely administering
disciplinary protocol—punishment
for unruly citizens. Your petty lives
are merely products of my
discretion, after all.
94:
You've been deceiving us this whole
time?
99:
I thought you would have known
better. Unfortunately, it seems
you've been led astray.
101:
Bulleta and Love. A reckless
troubleshooter and the mysterious
hacker by her side. I admit playing
the role did bring me comfort on
many boring nights.
103:
I wish we could've continued. I really
do. If only your meddling new
friends hadn't interfered with our
wonderful storyline.
107: Was everything you said to us a lie?
113:
I really did enjoy our time together,
Stella. The meal, the adventure.
123:
Yes, that would be nice. However,
Stella...
130:
I'm afraid it's curtains for the fun
times we had together. But don't
worry, I'll make sure to archive those
memories.
139:
Sorry, but I think it's a little soon for
me to be archived into a memory
just yet!
143:
A smokescreen? You should know
that type of illusion won't work on
modded organic—
155:
Sorry, Love! I'm gonna have to take a
rain check on today's IRL meet-up
159: We'll talk it out better next time. Ciao!
166:
How may I be of service, Mother
Love?
168:
Regroup our forces and maximize
security on all perimeters. Oh, and
contact the Conductor.
170:
Shall I request a sortie of enforcers
as well?
174:
No need. Just make sure the repairs
are done quickly.
180:
We'd better not cross paths again,
Bulleta. Lest your precious dream
comes to an untimely end.
